question:
District category contains Ancient City, and Manufacturing District.
Supermarkets category contains 99 Cents Only Stores, Sprouts Farmers Market, and Aldi (Germany).
Product category contains Alcoholic Beverages, and Plant-based Milk.
The number of each 99 Cents Only Stores 's Alcoholic Beverages equals each Ancient City 's Aldi (Germany).
The number of each 99 Cents Only Stores 's Plant-based Milk equals 19.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals 10 more than each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Alcoholic Beverages.
The number of each Ancient City 's Aldi (Germany) equals each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Product.
The number of each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Plant-based Milk equals 4 times each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Alcoholic Beverages.
The number of each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Alcoholic Beverages equals 8 more than each Aldi (Germany) 's Plant-based Milk.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Aldi (Germany) equals 5 times each Aldi (Germany) 's Alcoholic Beverages.
The number of each Aldi (Germany) 's Alcoholic Beverages equals 18 more than each Manufacturing District 's 99 Cents Only Stores.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Sprouts Farmers Market equals 1.
The number of each Aldi (Germany) 's Plant-based Milk equals 5 more than each Ancient City 's Sprouts Farmers Market.
The number of each Ancient City 's Sprouts Farmers Market equals 7.
The number of each Ancient City 's 99 Cents Only Stores equals 8.
How many Alcoholic Beverages does 99 Cents Only Stores have?
solution:
Define each Ancient City 's Sprouts Farmers Market as I; So I = 7.
Define each Aldi (Germany) 's Plant-based Milk as s; So s = 5 + I = 5 + 7 = 12.
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Alcoholic Beverages as m; So m = 8 + s = 8 + 12 = 20.
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Plant-based Milk as X; So X = 4 * m = 4 * 20 = 11.
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Product as h; So h = m + X = 20 + 11 = 8.
Define each Ancient City 's Aldi (Germany) as B; So B = h = 8.
Define each 99 Cents Only Stores 's Alcoholic Beverages as q; So q = B = 8.
